      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">52.219-7</ph> Notice of Partial
Small Business Set-Aside.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
         <p id="d3273e13" rev="FAC 2020-05 March 30, 2020" class="- topic/p "><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2014-002?>As
prescribed in <xref href="FAR-i1100931.dita#i1100931"
                  outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                  class="- topic/xref ">19.507</xref>(d), insert the
following clause:<?FM MARKER [Why] Amend section 52.219-7 by—
a. Revising the introductory text and the date of the clause;?></p>
         <p rev="FAC 2020-05 March 30, 2020"
            outputclass="Ctr_SmCaps"
            class="- topic/p ">Notice
of Partial Small Business Set-Aside (Mar 2020)</p>
         <ol id="d3243e25" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d3273e29" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
                  
                  
                  <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Definitions</i>.
“Small business concern,” as used in this clause, means a concern,
including its affiliates, that is independently owned and operated,
not dominant in the field of operation in which it is bidding on
Government contracts, and qualified as a small business under the
size standards in this solicitation.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d3273e41" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
                  
                  
                  <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Applicability.</i> 
                  <ph rev="FAC 2020-05 March 30, 2020" class="- topic/ph "><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2014-002?>This clause applies only
to contracts that have been partially set aside for small business
concerns.<?FM MARKER [Why] b. Revising paragraphs (b) and?></ph>
               </p>
            </li>
            <li props="Runin" class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d3273e98" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(c)</ph>
                  
                   General.</p>
               <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="id203J90L0DY4" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        
                        
                        <ph rev="FAC 2020-05 March 30, 2020" class="- topic/ph "><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2014-002?>A portion of this requirement,
identified elsewhere in this solicitation, has been set aside for
award to one or more small business concerns identified in 19.000(a)(3).
Offers received from concerns that do not qualify as small business
concerns shall be considered nonresponsive and shall be rejected
on the set-aside portion of the requirement.<?FM MARKER [Why] (c);?></ph>
                     </p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="id203J90L0NHS" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        
                        
                        <ph rev="FAC 2020-05 March 30, 2020" class="- topic/ph ">Small business concerns may
submit offers and compete for the non-set-aside portion and the
set-aside portion.</ph>
                     </p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="id203J90T04UI" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(d)</ph>
                  
                  
                  <ph rev="FAC 2020-05 March 30, 2020" class="- topic/ph "><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2014-002?>The Offeror shall—<?FM MARKER [Why] c. Adding paragraphs (d) and?></ph>
               </p>
               <p id="id203J9C00WHT" outputclass="List2" class="- topic/p ">[<i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Contracting Officer
check as appropriate.</i>]<ph rev="FAC 2020-05 March 30, 2020" class="- topic/ph "> </ph>
               </p>
               <p id="id203J9C020PF" outputclass="List2" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph rev="FAC 2020-05 March 30, 2020" class="- topic/ph ">_ Submit a separate offer
for each portion of the solicitation for which it wants to compete
(i.e. set-aside portion, non-set-aside portion, or both); or</ph>
               </p>
               <p id="id203J9C060PN" outputclass="List2" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph rev="FAC 2020-05 March 30, 2020" class="- topic/ph ">_ Submit one offer to include
all portions for which it wants to compete.</ph>
               </p>
            </li>
            <li props="Runin" class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="id203J90T0BYK" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(e)</ph>
                  
                  
                  <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Partial
set-asides of multiple-award contracts.</i>
               </p>
               <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="id203J9L00V7Q" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        
                        
                        <ph rev="FAC 2020-05 March 30, 2020" class="- topic/ph "><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2014-002?>Small business concerns will
not compete against other than small business concerns for any order
issued under the part or parts of the multiple-award contract that
are set aside.<?FM MARKER [Why] (e);?></ph>
                     </p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="id203J9L00030" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        
                        
                        <ph rev="FAC 2020-05 March 30, 2020" class="- topic/ph ">Small business concerns may
compete for orders issued under the part or parts of the multiple-award
contract that are not set aside, if the small business concern received
a contract award for the non-set-aside portion.</ph>
                     </p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
         </ol>
         <p outputclass="Endofclause" class="- topic/p ">(End of clause)</p>
         <section outputclass="Alternate" class="- topic/section "><?FM MARKER [Alt] Start?> 
            <p id="id203O80U005Z"
               rev="FAC 2020-05 March 30, 2020"
               class="- topic/p "><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2014-002?>
               <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Alternate I (Mar 2020)</i>.
As prescribed in <xref href="FAR-i1100931.dita#i1100931"
                     base="i1100931"
                     outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                     class="- topic/xref ">19.507</xref>(d),
add the following paragraph (f) to the basic clause:<?FM MARKER [Why] d. Removing Alternate I; and
e. Redesignating Alternate II as Alternate I and revising it.?></p>
            <p rev="FAC 2020-05 March 30, 2020"
               outputclass="List1"
               class="- topic/p ">(f)
Notwithstanding paragraph (c) of this clause, offers from Federal
Prison Industries, Inc., will be solicited and considered for both
the set-aside and non-set-aside portion of this requirement.</p> 
            <?FM MARKER [Alt] End?>
         </section>
      </conbody>
